1
00:00:02,206 --> 00:00:04,890
<i>Well, it's been about a month since we started school,</i>

2
00:00:05,118 --> 00:00:08,070
<i>and I've been enjoying my early
morning hikes about as much as I could.</i>

3
00:00:08,509 --> 00:00:10,469
<i>Although, I sort of feel like Sisyphus,</i>

4
00:00:10,770 --> 00:00:14,331
<i>cursed to forever roll that boulder up
the hill, tryin' to make it to the top.</i>

5
00:00:14,893 --> 00:00:16,158
<i>And then something hit me.</i>

6
00:00:16,427 --> 00:00:18,549
<i>Something that felt like an 8.0 earthquake,</i>

7
00:00:18,772 --> 00:00:21,393
<i>which brought my normal life to a grinding halt.</i>

8
00:00:22,713 --> 00:00:24,564
<i>No, that's not quite right.</i>

9
00:00:24,773 --> 00:00:26,739
<i>Actually, something was starting to happen.</i>

10
00:00:28,134 --> 00:00:31,293
If it doesn't exist, I should just make it myself!

11
00:00:31,697 --> 00:00:32,871
Make a club!

12
00:00:32,896 --> 00:00:34,639
And you're gonna help me with it!

13
00:00:35,024 --> 00:00:37,567
I've just figured out what we're gonna call ourselves!

14
00:00:38,130 --> 00:00:39,898
The SOS Brigade!

15
00:00:41,196 --> 00:00:43,548
And so begins my never-ending hell,

16
00:00:43,794 --> 00:00:46,257
thanks to the eccentric Haruhi Suzumiya.

17
00:00:46,971 --> 00:00:47,987
Good morning!

18
00:00:48,878 --> 00:00:50,346
Uh... Oh, morning.

19
00:00:50,371 --> 00:00:52,293
I forgot I had class duties today.

20
00:00:52,318 --> 00:00:54,947
I have to get the class log from the teacher's lounge.

21
00:00:55,384 --> 00:00:57,346
I have to hurry! I'll see you in class!

22
00:00:58,322 --> 00:01:01,629
<i>Hard to believe a girl like
that's in my class along with...</i>

23
00:01:04,814 --> 00:01:08,251
Hey, Kyon! Can you think of anything
else we're gonna need right now?

24
00:01:08,276 --> 00:01:09,026
What do you mean?

25
00:01:09,051 --> 00:01:11,805
I wanna get my hands on a mysterious transfer student.

26
00:01:11,878 --> 00:01:12,911
What do you think of that?

27
00:01:12,992 --> 00:01:16,645
I beg you, please start the
conversation by making the context clear.

28
00:01:16,758 --> 00:01:19,102
It's exactly what the SOS Brigade needs.

29
00:01:19,133 --> 00:01:21,627
We need something like a mysterious transfer student.

30
00:01:21,652 --> 00:01:23,383
Okay, before you kidnap anyone else,

31
00:01:23,414 --> 00:01:24,973
what do you mean by "mysterious"?

32
00:01:24,998 --> 00:01:27,959
Check it out. School started
less than two months ago, right?

33
00:01:27,984 --> 00:01:32,510
So I'm thinking that anybody who transfers
into our school right now has to be mysterious!

34
00:01:32,621 --> 00:01:33,391
Am I right?

35
00:01:33,534 --> 00:01:36,054
Maybe the kid's dad got relocated because of work.

36
00:01:36,079 --> 00:01:38,358
Oh, work with me here. It's not normal!

37
00:01:38,383 --> 00:01:40,352
I'd sorta like to know what you consider normal,

38
00:01:40,377 --> 00:01:41,820
but I'm almost afraid to ask.

39
00:01:41,845 --> 00:01:44,381
Hmm... I wonder if we'll get anyone like that.

40
00:01:44,437 --> 00:01:46,576
A mysterious transfer student...

41
00:01:47,028 --> 00:01:50,384
I guess in other words, you don't really
give a damn about anything I say at all.

42
00:01:50,999 --> 00:01:51,815
Whatever...

43
00:03:24,091 --> 00:03:28,394
<i>Apparently there's a rumor floating around
school that Haruhi and I are up to something.</i>

44
00:03:29,132 --> 00:03:31,713
Level with me. What are you and Suzumiya up to?

45
00:03:31,911 --> 00:03:34,683
You guys wouldn't happen to be
dating or anything, would you?

46
00:03:34,708 --> 00:03:36,401
Ugh, no, we're not dating.

47
00:03:36,512 --> 00:03:39,460
And trust me, I'd also like to
know what we're supposedly up to.

48
00:03:39,548 --> 00:03:41,725
I don't have any idea what I'm doing anymore.

49
00:03:41,852 --> 00:03:45,004
Just don't overdo it. You're not in junior high anymore.

50
00:03:45,029 --> 00:03:48,896
You guys mess up the school or anything,
you'll get suspended at the very least.

51
00:03:50,184 --> 00:03:55,057
<i>At least I can keep Yuki Nagato and Mikuru
Asahina from getting involved in anything too crazy.</i>

52
00:03:57,041 --> 00:03:59,154
<i>Since the SOS Brigade was founded,</i>

53
00:03:59,179 --> 00:04:03,254
<i>the once empty room of the former
literary club now has lots of things in it.</i>

54
00:04:03,993 --> 00:04:06,067
<i>Maybe she's planning on living here or something.</i>

55
00:04:07,624 --> 00:04:10,443
You know what? It'd be great to have a computer in here!

56
00:04:11,779 --> 00:04:16,443
We're living in the information age and we
don't even have a computer. I can't forgive them.

57
00:04:16,468 --> 00:04:18,231
<i>And who is it you can't forgive?</i>

58
00:04:19,485 --> 00:04:20,940
What d'ya say? Let's go get one!

59
00:04:20,965 --> 00:04:23,013
Do you have any idea how we're gonna get one?

60
00:04:23,156 --> 00:04:25,134
You're not gonna rob a computer store, are you?

61
00:04:25,293 --> 00:04:28,178
No way! We're gonna hit some place closer.

62
00:04:29,503 --> 00:04:31,259
Hi, everyone!

63
00:04:31,299 --> 00:04:36,122
I've come for a computer and all
the accessories that go with it!

64
00:04:36,868 --> 00:04:38,131
Who in here's the president?

65
00:04:38,156 --> 00:04:39,570
I guess that'd be me?

66
00:04:40,396 --> 00:04:44,473
There's only one reason why I would schlep
all the way over here to the computer club.

67
00:04:44,647 --> 00:04:46,115
I'm here for a computer!

68
00:04:46,140 --> 00:04:47,022
I only need one.

69
00:04:47,047 --> 00:04:49,355
Excuse me? You crazy or somethin'?

70
00:04:49,380 --> 00:04:52,415
We only need one, and you guys got a whole bunch in here.

71
00:04:52,440 --> 00:04:54,846
Hang on a sec, who the heck are you anyway?

72
00:04:54,871 --> 00:04:58,395
We are the SOS Brigade, and
I'm Haruhi Suzumiya, the leader!

73
00:04:58,431 --> 00:05:01,130
And these are my henchmen Number 1 and Number 2!

74
00:05:02,347 --> 00:05:05,700
Don't give me any crap. Just hand
over a computer and no one gets hurt.

75
00:05:05,819 --> 00:05:07,042
Why the hell should I?!

76
00:05:07,067 --> 00:05:08,821
I'm not givin' you guys anything!

77
00:05:12,074 --> 00:05:15,298
Okay. Here's how this is gonna go down, boys,

78
00:05:15,323 --> 00:05:16,870
so try to pay attention.

79
00:05:30,012 --> 00:05:31,092
What're you doing?!

80
00:05:31,890 --> 00:05:34,120
