241
00:14:21,999 --> 00:14:23,239
Who do they think they are?!

242
00:14:23,556 --> 00:14:26,970
<i>If two girls in bunny suits are
passing out flyers in front of the school,</i>

243
00:14:26,995 --> 00:14:29,006
<i>everybody'd come running to check that out.</i>

244
00:14:29,387 --> 00:14:32,273
Mikuru starts sobbing, I get yanked into detention,

245
00:14:32,329 --> 00:14:35,649
and Okabe, that handball freak, comes over... Augh!

246
00:14:36,452 --> 00:14:39,074
<i>I'm sure they didn't know what
to keep their eyes focused on.</i>

247
00:14:40,812 --> 00:14:42,481
Well, I guess that's it for today.

248
00:14:42,788 --> 00:14:43,746
Dismissed!

249
00:14:45,740 --> 00:14:47,549
How long you gonna cry anyway?!

250
00:14:47,676 --> 00:14:49,837
Let's go! Take it off, come on!

251
00:14:58,490 --> 00:14:59,929
Um, say, Kyon...

252
00:15:00,112 --> 00:15:03,227
If I find I'm unable to get married after all this,

253
00:15:03,401 --> 00:15:05,330
would you be willing to marry me...?

254
00:15:10,655 --> 00:15:11,671
<i>What should I say?</i>

255
00:15:12,250 --> 00:15:16,390
<i>Miss Asahina, you look like you just found
out you didn't get accepted into college.</i>

256
00:15:16,691 --> 00:15:20,673
<i>Or, like someone who's just lost her
job the day after buying her dream house.</i>

257
00:15:21,665 --> 00:15:25,239
<i>Wait... Oh man, now you're calling me Kyon, too...</i>

258
00:15:27,237 --> 00:15:30,897
<i>By the next day, the name Haruhi
Suzumiya had become infamous.</i>

259
00:15:30,922 --> 00:15:33,099
<i>Now everyone at school was talking about her.</i>

260
00:15:34,337 --> 00:15:37,943
Hey there, Kyon, hate to say it, but
it looks like you've gone and done it.

261
00:15:37,968 --> 00:15:40,822
You've become one of Suzumiya's gang of weirdos, huh?

262
00:15:40,900 --> 00:15:41,871
Oh, shut up.

263
00:15:42,388 --> 00:15:45,926
<i>The sucky thing about being part of all
this is that my name and Miss Asahina's</i>

264
00:15:45,951 --> 00:15:47,909
<i> are now floating around the campus, too.</i>

265
00:15:48,195 --> 00:15:49,982
I couldn't believe what I was seeing yesterday.

266
00:15:50,183 --> 00:15:52,953
A couple of bunny girls hanging
out by the school's main gate.

267
00:15:53,118 --> 00:15:56,384
I mean, the girl in red was Mikuru Asahina, wasn't it?

268
00:15:56,473 --> 00:15:59,364
Now everybody in school's talking about you guys, Kyon.

269
00:15:59,389 --> 00:15:59,928
Everybody.

270
00:15:59,953 --> 00:16:02,547
What exactly is this SOS Brigade?

271
00:16:04,172 --> 00:16:05,927
You're gonna have to ask Suzumiya.

272
00:16:06,125 --> 00:16:08,326
I really don't know. I don't even wanna know.

273
00:16:08,564 --> 00:16:11,702
Well, it definitely looks like
you guys are having a lot of fun.

274
00:16:11,727 --> 00:16:14,595
But you know, yesterday's stunt was a little overboard.

275
00:16:15,444 --> 00:16:18,742
<i>That day Miss Asahina didn't show up to school.</i>

276
00:16:19,885 --> 00:16:23,232
Unbelievable. Not a single email after all that publicity!

277
00:16:23,367 --> 00:16:27,765
<i>After publicity like that, I don't think
anyone's gonna want anything to do with us.</i>

278
00:16:27,790 --> 00:16:30,408
<i>Have to admit though, that
stunt caught everyone's attention.</i>

279
00:16:30,914 --> 00:16:32,946
Hang on... Where's Mikuru?

280
00:16:33,208 --> 00:16:34,514
Didn't she come to school?

281
00:16:34,539 --> 00:16:36,120
<i>She might never show up again.</i>

282
00:16:36,509 --> 00:16:38,667
<i>Hope she wasn't too traumatized by all this...</i>

283
00:16:38,692 --> 00:16:41,812
And I even got a new outfit for her to wear today, too.

284
00:16:41,837 --> 00:16:43,245
Why don't you wear it yourself then?

285
00:16:43,475 --> 00:16:45,469
Oh, don't worry, I'm gonna wear it.

286
00:16:45,659 --> 00:16:48,192
It's just not any fun if Mikuru isn't here...

287
00:16:48,567 --> 00:16:50,175
<i>Why don't you have Nagato wear it?</i>

288
00:16:50,378 --> 00:16:51,913
<i>I doubt she'd have any complaints.</i>

289
00:16:52,403 --> 00:16:54,881
<i>In fact, I don't think I'd mind seeing her wear it.</i>

290
00:16:56,241 --> 00:16:57,217
Agh!

291
00:16:57,888 --> 00:17:01,430
I got the SOS Brigade up and running,
and now we're just sitting around.

292
00:17:01,494 --> 00:17:04,122
What is it, everybody holding out on me or something?

293
00:17:04,147 --> 00:17:06,070
Keeping their mysteries to themselves...

294
00:17:06,356 --> 00:17:11,496
<i>Okay, Haruhi. Look, ask anybody in this
room and they'd say, "Sure, mysteries? Why not?"</i>

295
00:17:11,663 --> 00:17:14,793
<i>But an ordinary high school like ours
isn't gonna have a bunch of weirdness...</i>

296
00:17:14,818 --> 00:17:16,812
<i>... just stacked in the corner somewhere for you.</i>

297
00:17:17,248 --> 00:17:18,449
<i>You know that, right?</i>

298
00:17:18,671 --> 00:17:20,800
<i>I mean, you do realize that, don't you?</i>

299
00:17:21,070 --> 00:17:25,165
<i>You don't have any place to channel all
that adolescent frustration boiling inside you.</i>

300
00:17:25,379 --> 00:17:27,993
<i>Isn't that what's really fueling
all this impulsive behavior?</i>

301
00:17:28,263 --> 00:17:32,737
<i>Snap out of it and go find yourself a good-looking
guy and let him walk you home from school.</i>

302
00:17:32,832 --> 00:17:35,763
<i>Heck, go see a movie with him on Sunday or something.</i>

303
00:17:35,788 --> 00:17:37,511
<i>Or, why don't you try sports?</i>

304
00:17:37,536 --> 00:17:40,094
<i>Get on one of the teams and
give 'em hell out on the field.</i>

305
00:17:40,189 --> 00:17:42,937
<i>I'm sure you'll make the starting
line up on any varsity team you pick.</i>

306
00:17:42,962 --> 00:17:44,312
I'm going home.

307
00:17:52,926 --> 00:17:55,101
Well, guess I'll head out, too.

308
00:17:56,117 --> 00:17:57,197
Did you read it...?

309
00:17:58,381 --> 00:17:58,804
What?

310
00:18:00,782 --> 00:18:01,369
Book...

311
00:18:01,980 --> 00:18:03,859
Oh, no I haven't yet.

312
00:18:04,173 --> 00:18:05,820
Do you want me to give it back to you?

313
00:18:05,883 --> 00:18:07,670
That will not be necessary...

314
00:18:07,773 --> 00:18:12,277
When Yuki does talk, she has a tendency
to avoid the pitfalls of idle conversation.

315
00:18:12,302 --> 00:18:13,804
Please read it today...

316
00:18:14,693 --> 00:18:16,216
As soon as you get home...

317
00:18:18,814 --> 00:18:20,111
All right, I will.

318
00:18:39,698 --> 00:18:42,205
Huh! Where're you going now, Kyon?

319
00:18:42,230 --> 00:18:45,092
I'm meeting with someone at the station,
and don't talk with your mouth full.

320
00:18:58,280 --> 00:19:00,592
I'm sorry... Was today the day?

321
00:19:01,966 --> 00:19:04,642
You weren't waiting for me
here last night as well, were you?

322
00:19:05,675 --> 00:19:07,467
Well, why'd you pick this place to meet up?

323
00:19:07,987 --> 00:19:08,828
Follow me...

324
00:19:28,901 --> 00:19:32,317
So, uh... Where're your folks?

325
00:19:32,695 --> 00:19:33,753
They're not here...

326
00:19:34,285 --> 00:19:37,695
Uh... Yeah, I know they're not here right now, but,

327
00:19:38,266 --> 00:19:39,544
did they go somewhere?

328
00:19:39,901 --> 00:19:42,771
Actually, I am the only one who is ever here...

329
00:19:42,922 --> 00:19:44,190
You live by yourself?

330
00:19:44,215 --> 00:19:44,958
Yes...

331
00:19:46,942 --> 00:19:49,217
So what is it you wanted to see me about?

332
00:19:54,101 --> 00:19:54,903
Drink it...

333
00:19:59,576 --> 00:20:00,743
Is it good?

334
00:20:03,595 --> 00:20:04,634
Yeah, thanks.

335
00:20:30,417 --> 00:20:31,943
<i>I'm gonna explode...</i>

336
00:20:32,554 --> 00:20:37,900
Okay... You think it's about time you got around to
tell why you wanted me to come all the way out here?

337
00:20:40,667 --> 00:20:43,923
Were you uncomfortable talking to
me at school about it or something?

338
00:20:50,103 --> 00:20:52,431
It's about Haruhi Suzumiya.

339
00:20:53,145 --> 00:20:57,071
And, in addition, it is about myself...

340
00:20:58,301 --> 00:21:00,591
That is what I would like to talk about.

341
00:21:02,817 --> 00:21:05,740
Okay... You and Suzumiya. So what's up?

342
00:21:09,697 --> 00:21:12,072
It is difficult to find the words...

343
00:21:12,390 --> 00:21:15,726
There might be discrepancies in the transmission of data.

344
00:21:16,163 --> 00:21:18,676
However, please listen...

345
00:21:20,882 --> 00:21:24,822
Haruhi Suzumiya and I are not ordinary human beings...

346
00:21:24,918 --> 00:21:27,914
Yeah, I already sorta figured out
that you two weren't exactly normal.

347
00:21:27,939 --> 00:21:29,344
That's not what I mean...

348
00:21:31,808 --> 00:21:36,948
I am not referring to the absence of
universally accepted personality traits.

349
00:21:37,106 --> 00:21:42,398
What I mean is literal, in that she and I
are not the same as ordinary human beings.

350
00:21:42,501 --> 00:21:44,512
Human beings such as yourself.

351
00:21:44,908 --> 00:21:50,147
I have been created by the data integration
thought entity that supervises this galaxy.

352
00:21:50,399 --> 00:21:55,443
I am a humanoid interface designed to
make contact with organic lifeforms like you.

353
00:21:56,429 --> 00:21:57,866
Do you understand?

354
00:22:00,116 --> 00:22:00,735
Huh...?

355
00:22:00,987 --> 00:22:04,189
To use a common term that is applicable to this situation,

356
00:22:04,340 --> 00:22:07,068
I believe I would be classified as an alien.

357
00:22:10,682 --> 00:22:12,539
An... alien.

